    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 997.1 Carrera features the high-revving 3.6L M97 horizontally opposed six-cylinder, delivering a linear torque curve and exceptional throttle response. The G97 six-speed manual transaxle provides precise gate engagement, paired with a chassis utilizing Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM) to optimize damping rates for varied lateral loads. Crucially, this example has undergone an LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and proactive Air-Oil Separator (AOS) replacement, addressing key M97 architecture vulnerabilities. The braking system retains its factory-spec four-piston monoblock calipers for consistent thermal management, while the multi-link rear suspension geometry remains tight, ensuring the communicative rear-engine weight bias is fully exploitable. A mechanically sorted driver's car for the technical purist.",
